Title : Božidar Finka
Text : '''Božidar Finka''' (19 December 1925, [[Sali, Croatia|Sali]], [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]] – 17 May 1999) was a [[Croatia]]n linguist and lexicographer.

Finka's most significant work was in the fields of Croatian and Slavic [[dialectology]] and [[toponymy]]. With [[Stjepan Babić]] and [[Milan Moguš]], he co-authored ''Hrvatski pravopis'' ("Croatian Orthography", 1st ed. 1971).

Finka spent most of his scientific career working at the [[Institute of Croatian Language and Linguistics]], serving as its director from 1973–77. He was a full member of the [[Croatian Academy of Sciences and Arts]] since 1988.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://info.hazu.hr/en/member_of_academy/personal_pages/bozidar_finka_en | title=Božidar Finka, F.C.A. | work=info.hazu.hr | publisher=[[Croatian Academy of Sciences and Arts]] | language=Croatian | accessdate=4 April 2015}}</ref>

